{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17646807","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17646807"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T20:36:55+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T20:36:55+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18210"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18210","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18210"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10924"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"77630"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10924","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10924"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18210"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63144"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4936"},{"type":"tags","id":"4943"},{"type":"tags","id":"5296"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"25392"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25395"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"77630","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/77630"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following medications, when added to methotrexate, increases the risk of neutropaenia and should be avoided if creatinine clearance is less than 30 mL/min?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Leflunomide","Etanercept","Belimumab","Anakinra","Abatacept"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELeflunomide\u003C/strong\u003E is often used in combination with methotrexate for the treatment of rheumatoid arthritis. However, this combination can increase the risk of neutropaenia. Additionally, leflunomide should be avoided in patients with creatinine clearance less than 30 mL/min due to potential toxicity.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EEtanercept\u003C/strong\u003E - This is a biologic agent that does not typically increase the risk of neutropaenia when used with methotrexate.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBelimumab\u003C/strong\u003E - This is used for systemic lupus erythematosus and is not commonly combined with methotrexate for rheumatoid arthritis.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAnakinra\u003C/strong\u003E - This is an interleukin-1 receptor antagonist and does not have the same renal clearance concerns as leflunomide.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAbatacept\u003C/strong\u003E - This is a T-cell co-stimulation modulator and does not typically increase the risk of neutropaenia when used with methotrexate.\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Leflunomide is often used in combination with methotrexate for the treatment of rheumatoid arthritis.","Leflunomide can increase the risk of neutropaenia when used with methotrexate.","Leflunomide should be avoided in patients with creatinine clearance less than 30 mL/min due to potential toxicity."],"references":["Padda IS, Goyal A. Leflunomide. 2023 Jun 3. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 32491731","Tian H, Cronstein BN. Understanding the mechanisms of action of methotrexate: implications for the treatment of rheumatoid arthritis. Bull NYU Hosp Jt Dis. 2007;65(3):168-73. PMID: 17922664","Waller, D. G., \u0026 Hitchings, A. W. (2021). Medical Pharmacology and Therapeutics E-Book: Medical Pharmacology and Therapeutics E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Tashjian, A. H., \u0026 Armstrong, E. J. (2011). Principles of pharmacology: the pathophysiologic basis of drug therapy. Lippincott Williams \u0026 Wilkins","Queremel Milani DA, Davis DD. Pain Management Medications. 2023 Jul 3. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 32809527","Yu, L., Luo, R., Qin, G. et al. Efficacy and safety of anti-interleukin-1 therapeutics in the treatment of knee osteoarthritis: a systematic review and meta-analysis of randomized controlled trials. J Orthop Surg Res 18, 100 (2023). https://doi.org/10.1186/s13018-023-03590-2","Padda IS, Goyal A. Leflunomide. 2023 Jun 3. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 32491731."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63144"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18210"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63144","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/63144"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-07T20:44:46+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-08T00:06:51+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10924"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"77630"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":